            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$g''(0) = a^2 + 3$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$g''(0) = a^2 e^0 + f''(0) = a^2 + 3$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "The function $h$ is given by $h(x) = \\cos(kx) \\cdot f(x)$ for all real numbers, where $k$ is a constant. Find $h'(x)$ and write an equation for the line tangent to the graph of $h$ at $x = 0$.",
      "point_value": 5,
      "scoring_notes": "h'(x) = -k sin(kx) f(x) + cos(kx) f'(x). At x=0: h'(0) = -k sin(0) f(0) + cos(0) f'(0) = 0 + f'(0) = -4. h(0) = cos(0) f(0) = 1*2 = 2. Tangent line: y - 2 = -4(x - 0), i.e. y = -4x + 2.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct product rule setup: $h'(x) = -k\\sin(kx) \\cdot f(x) + \\cos(kx) \\cdot f'(x)$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$h'(x) = -k\\sin(kx) f(x) + \\cos(kx) f'(x)$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(x) = -k\\sin(kx) \\cdot f(x) + \\cos(kx) \\cdot f'(x)$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Evaluates $h(0) = \\cos(0) \\cdot f(0) = 1 \\cdot 2 = 2$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$h(0) = \\cos(0) \\cdot f(0) = 2$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Evaluates $h'(0) = -k\\sin(0) \\cdot f(0) + \\cos(0) \\cdot f'(0) = 0 + f'(0) = -4$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$h'(0) = 0 + 1 \\cdot f'(0) = -4$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(0) = -k(0)(2) + (1)(-4) = -4$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b4",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct tangent line equation using point $(0, 2)$ and slope $-4$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$y - 2 = -4(x - 0)$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$y = -4x + 2$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b5",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Notes that $h'(0) = -4$ is independent of $k$ (the $k$ term vanishes since $\\sin(0) = 0$)",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "The tangent line $y = -4x + 2$ is the same for all values of $k$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "Since $\\sin(k \\cdot 0) = 0$ for any $k$, the slope $h'(0) = -4$ regardless of $k$; tangent line: $y = -4x + 2$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
